'''Japanese Architecture and Art Net Users System''' or JAANUS is an online dictionary of [[Japanese architecture]] and [[Japanese art|art]] terms compiled by Dr. Mary Neighbour Parent. It contains approximately eight thousand entries.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.soas.ac.uk/library/subjects/artarch/references/ |title=Art & archaeology reference sources |publisher=[[School of Oriental and African Studies]] |accessdate=5 August 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130104224041/http://www.soas.ac.uk/library/subjects/artarch/references/ |archivedate= 4 January 2013 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite book |title=The Roof in Japanese Buddhist Architecture |author=Parent, Mary Neighbour |publisher=[[Weatherhill]] |year=1983 |isbn=0-8348-0186-8 |page=348}}</ref> It is searchable in both [[English language|English]] and [[romaji]] and contains many [[hyperlinks]] and [[illustrations]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.lib.washington.edu/types/dictionaries/G.html |title= Dictionaries |publisher=[[University of Washington]] |accessdate=5 August 2012}}</ref>
