{{short description|2007 book by Peter Goldie and Elisabeth Schellekens}} {{Infobox book | <!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject_Books --> | name = Philosophy and Conceptual Art | image = | caption = | authors = [[Peter Goldie]], [[Elisabeth Schellekens]] | country = | language = English | subject = [[aesthetics]] | publisher = [[Oxford University Press]] | pub_date = 2007 | media_type = Print ([[Paperback]]) | pages = 312 pp. | isbn = 9780199568253 }}
'''''Philosophy and Conceptual Art''''' is a 2007 book edited by [[Elisabeth Schellekens]] and [[Peter Goldie]]. The contributors deal with the philosophical questions raised by [[conceptual art]].<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Yanal |first1=Robert J. |title=Review of Philosophy and Conceptual Art |journal=Notre Dame Philosophical Reviews |date=30 May 2008 |url=https://ndpr.nd.edu/news/philosophy-and-conceptual-art/ |accessdate=23 November 2018 |issn=1538-1617}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Seeley |first1=William P. |title=Review of Philosophy and Conceptual Art |journal=[[The Journal of Aesthetics and Art Criticism]] |date=2008 |volume=66 |issue=2 |pages=203–205 |url=https://www.jstor.org/stable/40206331?seq=1#page_scan_tab_contents |accessdate=23 November 2018}}</ref>
